game_notes: Played through the entire game (with quarters!) Back in the late 90s as an 8 year old, myself, a fellow 3rd grade friend, and two of our summer camp junior counselors played through this game all the way at the arcade, rotating 2-and-2 when we died...just for the quality of the experience back then, this game gets 5 stars.
My most played game. 2156 hours tracked via Xfire, estimated 2000 more before/after the Xfire days.

game_title: Call of Duty: Black Ops II
game_notes: Master Prestige, Rank 6 Silver. I love CoD.
Woohoo! Black Ops and MW3 are still my games of choice.
6th prestige, level 41. Really cool campaign. Can''t wait to finish the first two games now so I know what just happened. XD
Let my cousin play it and now I can''t find it!? T_T Might need to rebuy. Just from what I gathered watching my cousin play, the game is fantastic.
ONE THOUSAND MILES.Actually turned out to be pretty fantastic once it grew on me. Screw Rally Raid. XD
Missions with Brando. XD After playing, 3, Showdown, and 1 in that order, 2 might actually be my favorite of them all. Even though I love all 4 in the series.
Rep 30, Fanbase 40. The best racing game I''ve played in a long, long time.
Racenet Team Championship. DiRT 3 definitely wins for realistic car control, but the fireworks and amazing gameplay make me fall in love with this spinoff. Another awesome racing game.

Treasure Hunter was merciless. I can''t even begin to describe how much I love this game. Everyone hated on the open world, but I thought the story should have more than made up for it, and I actually kinda liked the linearity.
Yellow 25 in multiplayer. Horrible collision, excellent and fun game, DLC costs way too much and I''m not paying for it.

game_title: Marvel vs. Capcom 3: Fate of Two Worlds
game_notes: Beat Arcade mode on Easy :P Worst game ever. Trololololololol XD such a rage game. Blast with friends, it''s really that simple. This game can and will make you hate things though.
Beat arcade mode or something. Bleh. Not really a Street Fighter kind of player. It's an okay game. More fun to watch high-level players.
Beat something. Bleh, I''m not much of a Tekken player. But I love Eddy!
I don't play this game. XD RAGE.
#1 Rank! :D Still need the other half of the achievements. I actually prefer the gameplay of the original Virtua Tennis for Dreamcast, but the career mode in this game is quite well done.

game_title: Super Mario Advance: Super Mario Bros. 2

game_notes: 8/8 super flags in 29:04! Absolute joy to play. Paper Mario strikes again!
Won R1 championship. Very solid racing game. Nearly perfect...just needs more track variety. Got very stale after season 3.
Legend is the final goal...Glitched achievement, GG. Completely different racing style from DiRT and Forza, but enjoyable. Not a fan of majorly glitched games, however.
Finished the game on Casual. Man...Casual was plenty tough enough for me. XD Great game, makes me want to play the sequels...
Level 23 multiplayer. Other than Virgin Media Endurance on Very Hard (aka impossible) this was a very enjoyable game. Time to wait for DiRT 4!
AC3 is better, but this was a fantastic game as well. ^_^

Fun stuff! Gonna work on completion soon. Typical Sonic game. Pretty easy to learn, hard to master. This one''s a bit generous in terms of difficulty, but extremely fun and something I look forward to playing again.
Thanks for the help Alex! Pretty fun game, if not a bit frustrating at times.

Inspired by the World Championships...28/50 in a row is my best so far. Kalos Champion in 31:21! Honestly, I never thought I''d play a game like Silver again. That perfect, polished feeling. The level curve could have been more challenging, but in the end, the multiplayer additions more than make up for it.
Missing about 100 colors. All plants. My 2nd favorite streetpass game. Fun!
